     SHORT="An anti-virus utility for Unix"
cat << EOF
Clam AntiVirus is an anti-virus toolkit for Unix. The main purpose of this 
software is the integration with mail servers (attachment scanning). The package 
provides a flexible and scalable multi-threaded daemon, a commandline scanner, and a 
tool for automatic updating via Internet. The programs are based on a shared library 
distributed with the Clam AntiVirus package, which you can use in your own software
EOF
